2025-12-08|Find Duplicate and Missing Number

Question
Given an unsorted array arr[] of size n, containing elements from the range 1 to n, it is known that one number in this range is missing, and another number occurs twice in the array, find both the duplicate number and the missing number.

Approach
1.	Iterate through arr:  
	- For each value x = abs(arr[i]):  
	  • Check arr[x−1].  
	  • If it’s already negative → x is duplicate.  
	  • Else flip it to negative to mark first visit.
2.	Second pass:  
	- The index i where arr[i] is still positive corresponds to missing = i + 1.
3.	Return {duplicate, missing}.  
4.	Time complexity: O(n).  
   Space complexity: O(1) extra (in-place marking).  

Solution
class Solution {
  public:
    vector<int> findTwoElement(vector<int>& arr) {

        int n = arr.size();
        int duplicate = -1, missing = -1;

        // Step 1: Find duplicate using marking method
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int x = abs(arr[i]);
            if (arr[x - 1] < 0) {
                duplicate = x;
            } else {
                arr[x - 1] = -arr[x - 1];
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find missing number
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] > 0) {
                missing = i + 1;
                break;
            }
        }

        return {duplicate, missing};
    }
};
